{"key":"processedPost-10277172","value":{"id":10277172,"first":10276232,"last":10277172,"when":1241359319,"utime":"05/03/09 05:01 PM","content":"Side pinning in tubs is caused by low humidity.&nbsp; The substrate pulls away from the edges as the mycelium colonizes it because it actually gets smaller.&nbsp; Fruits form in the high-humidity gap if your humidity on the surface is not high enough, or you're not misting, etc.&nbsp; The plastic trash bag liner helps somewhat because the substrate stays attached to the bag, thus the gap that forms is between the bag and the tub.&nbsp; It has nothing to do with light.<br />RR","title":"Re: side pinning","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}